msgid "Performance Settings"
msgstr "Configuración do rendemento"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:30
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kde;, is used on a wide variety of computers by a wide variety of users. "
#| "Under the category of performance, this dialog allows each user to adjust "
#| "options which may make the computer that &konqueror; is installed on feel "
#| "more responsive."
msgid ""
"&konqueror; is used on a wide variety of computers by a wide variety of "
"users. Under the category of performance, this dialog allows each user to "
"adjust options which may make the computer that &konqueror; is installed on "
"feel more responsive."
msgstr ""
"&kde; úsase en moi diversos computadores por usuarios moi diferentes. Na "
"categoría de rendemento agrúpanse os parámetros que cada usuario pode "
"axustar para facer que o computador no que está instalado o &konqueror; "
"responda máis á presa."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preloading"
msgstr "Precarga"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The subsection labeled <guilabel>Preloading</guilabel> also makes a "
#| "tradeoff between memory and performance."
msgid ""
"The subsection labeled <guilabel>Preloading</guilabel> makes a tradeoff "
"between memory and performance."
msgstr ""
"A subsección chamada <guilabel>Precarga</guilabel> tamén fai un balance "
"entre memoria e rendemento."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:35
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<emphasis>Preloading</emphasis> refers to loading an instance of "
#| "&konqueror; into memory before a user asks to start &konqueror;. The "
#| "positive effect of this is that when a user asks &kde; to load "
#| "&konqueror; the window appears instantly because most of the application "
#| "has been preloaded. The negative effect is that this instance of "
#| "&konqueror; uses memory that could be used by other programs. By default, "
#| "when a user closes &konqueror;, &kde; does not close the instance. This "
#| "means that the next time a user wants &konqueror; loaded, it is nearly "
#| "instantaneous again."
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Preloading</emphasis> refers to loading an instance of &konqueror; "
"into memory before a user asks to start &konqueror;. The positive effect of "
"this is that when a user asks to load &konqueror; the window appears "
"instantly because most of the application has been preloaded. The negative "
"effect is that this instance of &konqueror; uses memory that could be used "
"by other programs. By default, when a user closes &konqueror;, the instance "
"is not closed. This means that the next time a user wants &konqueror; "
"loaded, it is nearly instantaneous again."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Precargar</emphasis> refírese a cargar unha instancia do "
"&konqueror; na memoria antes de que o usuario inicie o programa. O efecto "
"positivo disto é que cando o usuario lle pida a &kde; que cargue o "
"&konqueror; a xanela hase mostrar instantaneamente porque a maior parte do "
"programa xa estará cargado. O efecto negativo é que esta instancia do "
"&konqueror; usa memoria que poderían usar outros programas. Por omisión, "
"cando un usuario pecha o &konqueror;, &kde; non pecha a instancia, deste "
"xeito a vindeira vez que o usuario cargue o &konqueror; abrirase ao momento."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:37
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The final check box labeled <guilabel>Always try to have at least one "
#| "preloaded instance</guilabel> signals to &kde; that you always want &kde; "
#| "to have one preloaded, but not used, instance of &konqueror; available. "
#| "This option will actually decrease performance on some machines "
#| "(especially those with limited physical memory)."
msgid ""
"The final check box labeled <guilabel>Always try to have at least one "
"preloaded instance</guilabel> signals that you always want to have one "
"preloaded, but not used, instance of &konqueror; available. This option will "
"actually decrease performance on some machines (especially those with "
"limited physical memory)."
msgstr ""
"A opción etiquetada como <guilabel>Tentar sempre ter polo menos unha sesión "
"precargada</guilabel> indícalle a &kde; que debe procurar ter unha sesión do "
"&konqueror; precargada pero non usaada. Nalgunhas máquinas esta opcións "
"reducirá o rendemento (especialmente nas que teñan pouca memoria)."

#~ msgid "&kde; 4.4"
#~ msgstr "&kde; 4.4"

#~ msgid "&konqueror; instances"
#~ msgstr "Instancias do &konqueror;"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The first section of this dialog is labeled <guilabel>Minimize Memory "
#~ "Usage</guilabel> and has three options which determine maximum number of "
#~ "instances of &konqueror; that can be open on one machine at any one time."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "A primeira sección deste diálogo chámase <guilabel>Minimizar o uso da "
#~ "memoria</guilabel> e ten tres opcións que determinan a cantidade máxima "
#~ "de instancias do &konqueror; que se poden abrir nunha máquina á vez."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Do not confuse &konqueror; instances, with &konqueror; windows or tabs. "
#~ "The number of &konqueror; instances is determined by &kde; not by the "
#~ "user. You can think of instances as the hidden data of your &konqueror; "
#~ "windows and tabs. One &konqueror; instance can contain the data for "
#~ "multiple windows or tabs. Your choice on the following radio buttons does "
#~ "not limit the number of windows you can open at one time, but rather, how "
#~ "many instances of &konqueror; you can have open."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Non confunda as instancias de &konqueror; coas súas xanelas ou lapelas, a "
#~ "cantidade de instancias determínaas &kde;, non o usuario. Pense nas "
#~ "instancias como en datos ocultos das xanelas e lapelas do  &konqueror;; "
#~ "Unha instancia pode conter os datos de varias xanelas ou lapelas. O que "
#~ "vostede escolla nestas alternativas non limita o número de xanelas que "
#~ "poida ter abertas á vez senón cantas instancias de &konqueror; pode ter "
#~ "abertas."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The reason the choices you make in this dialog box are important is "
#~ "evident when something goes wrong and &konqueror; is forced to close an "
#~ "instance. <emphasis>All &konqueror; windows associated with a &konqueror; "
#~ "instance must be closed immediatly (without time to save data or bookmark "
#~ "locations).</emphasis> Therefore, the more instances you can have open at "
#~ "one time, the less likely a problem in one instance will affect all of "
#~ "your work. Each instance requires more memory which can be a problem on "
#~ "systems with less system memory."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "O motivo polo que as escollas que faga neste diálogo son importantes é "
#~ "evidente cando algo vai mal en &konqueror; se ve forzado a pechar unha "
#~ "instancia: <emphasis>Todas as xanelas do &konqueror; asociadas con esa "
#~ "instancia pecharanse inmediatamente (sen darlle tempo a gardar datos nin "
#~ "marcadores)</emphasis>. Polo tanto, cantas máis instancias teña abertas á "
#~ "vez, menos probábel é que un problema nunha delas afecte a todo o seu "
#~ "traballo. Cada instancia consume algo de memoria, e isto pode ser un "
#~ "problema nos sistemas que teñan pouca."

#~ msgid "Your options are:"
#~ msgstr "As alternativas son:"

#~ msgid "Never"
#~ msgstr "Nunca"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "There are no restraints. Any number of &konqueror; instances can be open "
#~ "at any one time. The advantage of this option is if any &konqueror; "
#~ "instance crashes the remaining will be unaffected. The disadvantage is "
#~ "that each &konqueror; instance uses more memory."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Non hai restricións, poden abrirse cantas instancias do &konqueror; se "
#~ "queira á vez. A vantaxe desta opción é que se unha delas se pecha "
#~ "inesperadamente as demais non se verán afectadas. A desvantaxe é que cada "
#~ "unha delas consume algo de memoria."

#~ msgid "For file browsing only (recommended)"
#~ msgstr "Só para a navegación de ficheiros (recomendado)"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If this option is selected, you can have as many as you want &konqueror; "
#~ "instances open that are browsing the web, but only one instance of "
#~ "&konqueror; for file management."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Se escolle esta opción poderá ter cantas instancias do &konqueror; queira "
#~ "para navegar pola web, pero só unha para a xestión de ficheiros."

#~ msgid "Always (use with care)"
#~ msgstr "Sempre (empregar con coidado)"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If this option is selected, you can only have one instance of &konqueror; "
#~ "running at any one time. This saves system memory, but if your "
#~ "&konqueror; window crashes, all your browsing windows close immediatly "
#~ "without warning. This should only be used for seriously memory limited "
#~ "systems."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Se escolle esta opción só poderá ter unha instancia do &konqueror; en "
#~ "execución á vez. Isto aforra memoria, pero se a xanela se pecha "
#~ "inesperadamente todas as xanelas han pecharse inmediatamente sen gardar. "
#~ "Isto só debería usarse en sistemas con graves limitacións de memoria."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The spinbox labeled <guilabel>Maximum number of instances kept preloaded:"
#~ "</guilabel> can be used to adjust the maximum number of preloaded "
#~ "instances. This option does not affect instances when they are loaded. It "
#~ "also does not limit the number of instances that can be used by active "
#~ "windows. It only affects the number of preloaded instances."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "O selector etiquetado <guilabel>Número máximo de sesións precargadas:</"
#~ "guilabel> pode usarse para axustar a cantidade máxima de instancias que "
#~ "se poden precargar. Esta opción non afecta ás instancias cando se cargan, "
#~ "nin limita a cantidade das que se poden usar nas xanelas activas. Só "
#~ "afecta a cantidade de instancias precargadas."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The check box labeled <guilabel>Preload an instance after &kde; startup</"
#~ "guilabel> does just what it says. It tells &kde; to preload one instance "
#~ "of &konqueror; at the startup of &kde;."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "A opción etiquetada <guilabel>Precargar unha sesión despois do inicio do "
#~ "&kde;</guilabel> fai exactamente iso: indícalle a &kde; que cando se "
#~ "inicie precargue unha instancia do &konqueror;."

#~ msgid "This does extend the startup time for &kde;."
#~ msgstr "Isto aumenta o tempo de arranque do &kde;."
